Use the Lower button to move the window or icon at the pointer location
to the back of the workspace and tuck it behind any overlapping windows
and icons.

Press-drag-release mode:

	Drag MENU onto the button and release MENU to move the
	window or icon at the pointer location to the back of
	the workspace.

Stay-up mode:

	Click SELECT or MENU on the window menu button to post
	the window menu in stay-up mode. Move the pointer to the
	button and click SELECT.

You can bring a window or icon to the front of the screen by selecting it.
To select a window, move the pointer to the window title button or border
and click or press SELECT. To select an icon, move the pointer onto an
icon and click or press SELECT.
